Four more persons have died from COVID-19, bringing Ghana's total death toll to 320, the latest figures from the Ghana Health Service have revealed. The active caseload has also shot up from 488 to 566.

So far, a total of 48 055 cases have been confirmed nationwide since mid-March [2020], when the 1st 2 cases were discovered in the country. Out of that number, 47 169 have recovered.

